<br>
I have a question for you.<br>
<br>
I am currently sneaking up slowly on level 45.  I have been playing EQ for three years now [Finnigan was born in April, 200<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , and because of the realities of Real Life commitments, and personal play-style preferences, most of that time has been played soloing.<br>
<br>
I am just now starting to reach an EQ 'age' when Finnigan is starting to think about raiding.  I am ashamed to admit it, but because of all the time I have spent alone in Norrath, my self-education of a Ranger's proper role in group dynamics is sadly lacking. [*Finnigan hangs his head*]<br>
<br>
I have read a number of forums that give out general guide lines for anyone going on a raid:<br>
<br>
Listen to what you're told.<br>
Don't bother RL with unnecessary questions/comments.<br>
Don't use RL /shout channel.<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
I also have a GENERAL idea of what I should and should not do as a Ranger:<br>
<br>
Don't break mezz with snare.<br>
Don't take aggro off Main Tank.<br>
Provide protection for healers.<br>
'handle' adds.<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
What I really need some guidance on is the SPECIFIC ways I need to do my job:<br>
<br>
What is my spell selection?<br>
How do I protect clerics?<br>
Under what circumstances do I cast which spell?<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
I want to do a good job as a raid member, and have no wish to embarrass either myself, my guild, or my class by not knowing my job.<br>
<br>
Any specific guidelines you can give me would be most welcome.<br>
<br>
Finnigan<br>
