<br>
With the hot keys on a raid usually you have more than one assist though.  You should have one for MA, SA, and maybe even a third, but at that point often things have gone bad.<br>
<br>
Before the first battle, type /assist off.  This prevents auto-attack when you assist.  That way if the MA is roaming to various targets before he finally picks one to engage, you can keep hitting the assist key without breaking MeZ, but you also see what the MA has targetted.  Also, mash that assist key one more time when assist is called, this ensures you are on the correct MoB.<br>
<br>
Lots of warning about aggro in here.  I rarely have a problem if the MA is alive.  If he/she is alive, and doesn't call for assist until aggro is firmly established, you should be fine.  Remember others advice about not attacking until the MA asks you to though.  Perhaps if you are on early snares you might take some abuse but overall its better you take the abuse when the MA first engages then the chanter that mezzed.  In these cases make sure you are standing next to the MA so he/she doesn't have to chase the mob chasing you in order beat it and establish aggro.  Mostly, I only have to worry about aggro in group XP situations where we don't give the MA as long to establish aggro.<br>
<br>
I find the more important way to avoid damage is staying to the side or behind the mobs.  Learn to use CTRL and arrow keys to slide around the mob, that way you can keep your position to the side or behind, but keep connecting with your weapons the whole time.<br>
<br>
The archery advice given looks good to me.  I don't have EQ or AM so I am still using melee on raids and have no further comments there.<br>
<br>
<br>
